The method then creates an instance of the `Random` class to generate random characters. It initializes an empty list to store the password characters.

Next, it adds at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one digit, and one special character to the password list. This ensures that the password contains at least one of each required character type.

After that, the method randomly selects characters from the combined string of all available characters (lowercase, uppercase, digits, and special characters) and adds them to the password list until it reaches the desired length.

Finally, it shuffles the characters in the password list randomly to ensure the required characters are positioned at different locations within the password.

The generated password is then converted to a string and returned by the method. In the provided `main` method, the `generatePassword` method is called with a password length of 8, and the generated password is printed to the console.

