- The function first checks if the input `arr` is an array using `Array.isArray()`. If it is not, an error is thrown.
- Then, the function checks if the input `arr` is empty. If it is, the function immediately returns the empty array.
- Next, the function uses a for loop to iterate through the first half of the array (up to `Math.floor(arr.length / 2)`).
- Inside the loop, the function checks if both the current element and its corresponding element from the end of the array are integers. If either of them is not an integer, an error is thrown.
- If both elements are integers, the function swaps them by assigning the value of `arr[i]` to a temporary variable `temp`, then assigning the value of `arr[arr.length - i - 1]` to `arr[i]`, and finally assigning the value of `temp` to `arr[arr.length - i - 1]`.
